Aboitiz Power Corp., First Philippine: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-04T00:36:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/aboitiz-power-corp-first-philippine-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of noon yesterday
in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.6 percent to
3,834.05.    Aboitiz Equity Ventures Inc. (AEV)  : The company with
investments and finance said consolidated net income in the
fourth quarter more than doubled to 5 billion pesos ($115
million) from 2.4 billion pesos a year earlier, a statement to
the stock exchange showed. The stock rose 2.5 percent to 43.15
pesos.    Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  : The Philippine company that
owns  power plants  and electricity distributors said fourth-
quarter net profit in 2010 rose 249 percent to 6.5 billion pesos
from a year ago, boosted by higher volume sales and prices. The
stock gained 2.7 percent to 30.10 pesos.    First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)  : The company with
investments in power plants said it will pay a 1 peso cash
dividend, a stock exchange filing showed. The stock rose 0.6
percent to 54.20 pesos.    Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  : The Philippine
unit of Hong Kong-based First Pacific Co.’s dividend growth will
be “constrained” in the next four-to-five years as the company
and its units focus on expansion, President Jose Lim said. Metro
Pacific’s profit increased 25 percent to a record 2.87 billion
pesos last year, the company said yesterday. The stock advanced
0.6 percent to 3.47 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
